detaileddescription.para: This method destroys this ClientApp.
This method logs on the client.
This method sets the sendTimeReportThreshold of our server connection.
This method indicates if this ClientApp can generate movement updates for this entity.
This method indicates if a Movement Controller for this entity can be set.
This method sets a new default movement controller for this bot.
This method sets a new movement controller for this bot. On failure, the controller is left unchanged.
This method sets the position of the client.
This method gets the position of the client.
This method sets the direction of the client.
This method gets the direction of the client.
This method sets the yaw of the client.
This method gets the yaw of the client.
This method sets the pitch of the client.
This method gets the pitch of the client.
This method sets the roll of the client.
This method gets the roll of the client.
This method sets the entity's position and direction.

This method adds a timer for this bot. The callback will be executed during the next tick after the specified number of seconds has elapsed. The id of this timer is returned so it can be cancelled later on with delTimer() if desired. A negative return value indicates failure.
This method deletes a timer for this bot. It actually just adds the timer ID to a list of timers to be ignored so when the timer finally expires its callback is not executed.
Destructor.
This method sends a movement message to the server.
Returns the transport name of server connection uses.
This method returns whether or not the connection is active.
This method processes any timers that have elapsed
This method is called when we are logged off from the server.
This method is called when we fail to log into the server
Override from ServerMessageHandler, done for testing streaming downloads to multiple clients.
This method returns the static Watcher associated with this class.
This class is used to hold a connection to the server.
